-------------------------Message 1 ---------------------------------- 
Date: Wed, 10 Aug 2005 15:55:13
From: Heike Hoffmeister < heike.hoffmeister@scansoft.com >
Subject: Computational Linguistics/Portuguese: Junior Linguist, ScanSoft International, Gent, Belgium  
 

This announcement was accompanied by a donation to the LINGUIST List! 

University or Organization: ScanSoft International 
Department: R&D TTS
Job Rank: Junior Linguist  
Specialty Areas: Computational Linguistics; Portuguese
Required Language(s): Portuguese (POR)


Description:

ScanSoft Inc. is a publicly traded company (Nasdaq: SSFT) with offices
around the world. With more than 1000 employees, we are the market-leading
supplier of speech and imaging solutions that are used to automate a wide
range of manual processes - increasing productivity, reducing costs and
improving customer service.

ScanSoft is currently looking for support from a:

Portuguese Junior Linguist

Key Responsibilities: 
Your function will be to create a state-of-the-art voice for use with the
market-leading RealSpeak text-to-speech (TTS) engine. Some of your key
tasks will be:

- Research on SMS and design of an SMS pre-processor
- Design of text corpora for development and testing
- Creating and tuning the TTS voice
- Testing and productisation of the TTS voice


Your Profile:
We are looking for enthusiastic, dedicated people who want to learn about,
or increase their knowledge of, speech technology while making a real
contribution to a successful product. In terms of skills, we are seeking
people who can do most - but not necessarily all - of the following. 
If you:

- fluently speak standard Portuguese
- have some experience in working with speech and/or linguistics or related
fields (we're especially interested if you've studied phonetics) either in
academia or in industry
- have some computational ability - no programming is required, but you
should be comfortable working with MS Windows
- if you know some awk or Perl, it would be an advantage, but is not required.

- and if you can dedicate 2-4 weeks to this project (working from home or in
our Belgium headquarter), then we would love to hear from you.


Contact:
Please send your resume via email to scansoft@agents.icims.com with the
subject line being:    Job ID: 1228
   
We are looking forward to receiving your application! If you have any
questions, please contact Heike Hoffmeister, Manager International
Recruitment at 0049-241-8871 103.

Address for Applications: 

Heike Hoffmeister 
Kackertstr. 10 
Aachen 52072 
Germany  

Application Deadline: Open until filled.

Contact Information:

Heike Hoffmeister 
Email: heike.hoffmeister@scansoft.com 
Phone: +49-241 8871 103 
Website: http://www.scansoft.com





